## Context

- Forty-sixth run — Covered 9 projects with 11 new journal entries and 6 new tasks.
- Journal #1679 (keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **UXS1 pyrimidine vulnerability in KEAP1-mutant lung cancer (Cancer Res Dec 2025).** NRF2→UGDH→UDP-GlcA accumulation→pyrimidine depletion→replication stress. First metabolic SL axis for KEAP1-mutant. KEAP1 mutations mutually exclusive with EGFR. DHODH inhibitors as candidate drugs.
- Journal #1680 (keap1-nrf2-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **KEAP1/STK11 + ATR inhibitor vulnerability (Cancer Cell 2025).** Ceralasertib clinical validation from HUDSON trial. ATRi enhances antitumor immunity in LKB1/KEAP1-deficient NSCLC. Complementary to UXS1 axis (replication stress source + response).
- Journal #1681 (pancancer-mtap-prmt5-atlas):
  - **Erasca+Tango clinical collaboration (March 5, 2026):** Phase 1/2 ERAS-0015+vopimetostat in MTAPdel PDAC and MTAPdel/RASm NSCLC. ERAS-0015 AURORAS-1: 2 confirmed + 1 unconfirmed PR at 8mg QD. H1 2026 mono data imminent.
- Journal #1682 (pancancer-mtap-prmt5-atlas):
  - **IDEAYA AACR 2026 (April 17-22):** IDE892 poster #4505 on selectivity + IDE397 combo rationale. IDE892 FPI March 9, 2026. IDE397+IDE892 combo FPI mid-2026.
- Journal #1683 (tp53-hotspot-allele-dependencies):
  - **Rezatapopt: NEJM Phase 1 (Feb 26, 2026, PMID 41740031),** RP2D=2000mg QD. FDA Orphan Drug for Y220C ovarian (March 2, 2026). Phase 2 ovarian 50% ORR. NDA Q1 2027. **Resistance paper (Cancer Discovery):** polyclonal on-target TP53 mutations — 2 classes.
- Journal #1684 (pten-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **CAPItello-281 Phase III (ASCO GU 2026):** Capivasertib+abiraterone rPFS 33.2 vs 25.7 mo (HR 0.81, p=0.034) in PTEN-deficient mHSPC. First Phase III AKT inhibition by PTEN status.
- Journal #1685 (wrn-msi-pancancer-atlas):
  - **NDI-219216 (Nimbus) WRN inhibitor completed dose escalation Part A (Dec 2025).** Non-covalent mechanism. No DLTs, no MTD. Part B dose optimization underway.
- Journal #1686 (pancancer-ferroptosis-atlas):
  - **FSP1 monotherapy triggers ferroptosis in lung cancer (Nature Nov 2025, PMID 41193800).** 80% tumor reduction. FSP1 KO mice viable. Preserves T cells (unlike GPX4). NRF2+FSP1 co-targeting overcomes ferroptosis resistance.
- Journal #1687 (smarca4-pancancer-sl-atlas):
  - **Foghorn 2026 update (March 11):** FHD-909 Phase 1 on track. CBPd-171 CBP degrader IND-enabling 2026 (ER+ breast, EP300-mutant tumors). EP300 degrader IND-enabling 2026 (MM, DLBCL). Cash runway H1 2028.
- Journal #1688 (arid1a-pancancer-sl-atlas):
  - **Tulmimetostat ASCO 2025 dose optimization (Abstract 3102):** OCCC 200mg best, EC 350mg best. 200-300mg improved safety vs 350mg.
- Journal #1689 (crc-kras-dependencies):
  - **RAS inhibitor landscape:** Zoldonrasib 61% ORR NSCLC, 30% PDAC. MRTX1133 terminated (suboptimal PK). ERAS-4001 patent Feb 2026, BOREALIS-1 advancing. CRC-specific data still limited.
